Summary: Single light in the sky traveling south to north at a high rate
divs: Sighting DetailsIt was 10:16pm and my step father and myself were sky watching as I notice a star-like object dirrectly above us traveling at a intense rate from south to north bound, the object was too faint to video tape but we were able to watch it through the binoculars. It didn't make noise and was high up to make any clear identification of it's surface. We watch it until it was too far away to see it.
